i18n.icons.descriptions.flag.description: The flag icon represents a rectangular piece of fabric of distinctive design that is used as a symbol, as a signaling device, or as a decoration.
i18n.icons.descriptions.flag.do-not-use-: Like (heart icon), Alert/Notification (bell icon), Nation/Nationality (globe icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.flask.descriptio: The flask icon represents a narrow-necked glass container, typically conical or spherical, used in a laboratory to hold reagents or samples.
i18n.icons.descriptions.folder-open.desc: The open folder icon represents a open folding cover or holder, typically made of stiff paper or card, for storing loose papers.
i18n.icons.descriptions.folder-open.do-n: Folder (folder icon), Archive (archive icon), Inbox/Deopt (inbox icon), Collection of files (stack icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.folder.descripti: The folder icon represents a folding cover or holder, typically made of stiff paper or card, for storing loose papers.
i18n.icons.descriptions.folder.do-not-us: Open folder (folder-open icon), Archive (archive icon), Inbox/Deopt (inbox icon), Collection of files (stack icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.forward.descript: The forward icon represents sending or shipping onward from an intermediate station in transit.
i18n.icons.descriptions.forward.do-not-u: Reply (reply icon), File is forwared (file-forward icon), Move right (arrow icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.frown.descriptio: The frown icon represents an expression of displeasure.
i18n.icons.descriptions.gender-identity-: The agender icon represents the gender identity agender. A person who is agender does not identify with any particular gender, or they may have no gender at all.
The bigender icon represents the gender identity bigender. A person who identifies as bigender has two genders. People who are bigender often display cultural masculine and feminine roles.
The female icon represents the gender identity female.

The gender expansive icon represents the gender identity gender expansive. Gender expansive is an umbrella term used for individuals who broaden their own culture’s commonly held definitions of gender, including expectations for its expression, identities, roles, etc.
The male icon represents the gender identity male.

The neutrois icon represents the gender identity neutrois. Neutrois is a non-binary gender identity. There is no one definition of Neutrois, since each person that self-identifies as such experiences their gender differently.
The nonbinary icon represents the gender identity nonbinary. A person who identifies as nonbinary does not experience gender within the gender binary.
i18n.icons.descriptions.git-hub.descript: Used to indicate the usage of GitHub
i18n.icons.descriptions.git-hub.use-for: Link to GitHub page or indication that GitHub was part of the project
i18n.icons.descriptions.globe.descriptio: The globe icon represents the earth.
i18n.icons.descriptions.headphones.descr: The headphones icon represents an electrical device worn on the ear to receive a audio signal.
i18n.icons.descriptions.headphones.do-no: Audio (audio icon), Microphone (microphone icon), Call (phone icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.heart-filled.des: The filled heart icon represents a hollow muscular organ that pumps the blood through the circulatory system by rhythmic contraction and dilation.
i18n.icons.descriptions.heart-filled.do-: Like (heart icon), Positiv rating (thumbs-up icon), Good/Happyness (smile icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.heart.descriptio: The heart icon represents a hollow muscular organ that pumps the blood through the circulatory system by rhythmic contraction and dilation.
i18n.icons.descriptions.help-circle.desc: The help circle icon represents a punctuation mark (?) with a circular outline indicating additional help or information.
i18n.icons.descriptions.help.description: The help icon represents a punctuation mark (?) indicating a question, doubt or uncertainty about something.
i18n.icons.descriptions.history.descript: The history icon represents the whole series of past events connected with a particular person or thing.
i18n.icons.descriptions.home.description: The home icon represents the place where one lives permanently, especially as a member of a family or household.
i18n.icons.descriptions.horse.descriptio: The horse icon represents a horse, a four-legged plant-eating domesticated mammal with solid hoofs and a flowing mane and tail, used for riding, racing, and to carry and pull loads.
i18n.icons.descriptions.hospital.descrip: The Hospital icon represents a hospital building.
i18n.icons.descriptions.id-card.descript: The ID-Card icon represents a card bearing identifying data, such as age or organizational membership, about the individual whose name appears thereon.
i18n.icons.descriptions.id-card.do-not-u: Payment card (credit-card icon), Certificate (certificate icon), User (user icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.image.descriptio: The image icon represents a visible impression obtained by a camera, telescope, microscope, or other device, or displayed on a computer or video screen.
i18n.icons.descriptions.image.do-not-use: Image file (file-image icon), Take image (camera icon), Video (video icon), Show as diagram (chart icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.inbox.descriptio: The inbox icon represents a box or tray, as on a desk, for holding incoming mail or documents.
i18n.icons.descriptions.inbox.do-not-use: Archive (archive icon), Folder (folder icon), E-Mail (mail icon), Collection of files (stack icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.inbox.use-for: Inbox; Depot of work or tasks
i18n.icons.descriptions.increase.descrip: The increase icon represents a graph pointing upwards, indicating increase of something.
i18n.icons.descriptions.increase.do-not-: Arrow (arrow icon); Upload (upload icon); Bolt/Flash/Electricity (bolt icon); Increase in connection with charts (chart-increase icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.industry.descrip: The industry icon represents a building with facilities for manufacturing.
i18n.icons.descriptions.industry.do-not-: Office (building icon), Institution/University (university icon), Laboratory (flask icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.info-circle.desc: The info circle icon represents informativity or availability of additional information.
i18n.icons.descriptions.info.description: The info icon represents informativity or availability of additional information.
i18n.icons.descriptions.key.description: The key icon represents a small piece of shaped metal with incisions cut to fit the wards of a particular lock, which is inserted into a lock and turned to open or close it.
i18n.icons.descriptions.keyboard.descrip: The keyboard icon represents a group of systematically arranged keys by which a machine or device is operated.
i18n.icons.descriptions.language.descrip: The language icon represents a turnstile or a revolving door with a script-like 卡 and a sans-serif A.
i18n.icons.descriptions.language.do-not-: Regular language selection (DE/IT/FR/EN), Nationality (globe icon), Sign language (sign-language icon), Speech (speech-bubble icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.language.use-for: Switch language for multi-national / multi-language uses.
i18n.icons.descriptions.lifering.descrip: The lifering icon represents a buoyant support for keeping a person afloat in water.
i18n.icons.descriptions.link.description: The link icon represents two connected links of a chain.
i18n.icons.descriptions.link.do-not-use-: Link to external page or resource (external icon), Unlink (unlink icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.link.use-for: Link elements; Connect; Link to internal page or resource
i18n.icons.descriptions.list-paragraph.d: The list paragraph icon represents a list of or single legal text.
i18n.icons.descriptions.list.description: The list icon represents a simple series of words or numerals, such as the names of persons, objects or tasks.
i18n.icons.descriptions.list.do-not-use-: Depot of tasks (inbox icon), File containing lists (file-bullet icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.lock.description: The lock icon represents a removable lock with a shackle that can be passed through a staple or link and then secured.
i18n.icons.descriptions.lock.do-not-use-: Access (key icon), Unlock/Unlocked (unlock icon), Fix/Lock in position (pin icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.login.descriptio: The login icon represents the act of logging in to a computer, database, or system.
i18n.icons.descriptions.login.do-not-use: Inbox (inbox icon), Download (download icon), Logout (logout icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.logout.descripti: The logout icon represents the act of logging out of a computer, database, or system.
i18n.icons.descriptions.logout.do-not-us: Upload (upload icon), Login (login icon), External page or resource (external icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.low-vision.descr: The low vision icon represents partial blindness or the inability to see well.
i18n.icons.descriptions.low-vision.use-f: Visually impaired; Partial blindness; High contrast mode
i18n.icons.descriptions.magnet.descripti: The magnet icon represents a body having the property of attracting iron and producing a magnetic field external to itself.
i18n.icons.descriptions.mail-attachement: The icon is used to show that there is an option to attach a file to the mail.
i18n.icons.descriptions.map-marker.descr: The map marker icon represents an object used to indicate a position or place.
i18n.icons.descriptions.map-marker.do-no: Navigation (compass icon), World (globe icon), Map/Directions (pap icon), Home (home icon), Pinning/Make sticky (pin icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.map.description: The map icon represents a diagrammatic representation of an area of land or sea showing physical features, like cities or roads.
i18n.icons.descriptions.map.do-not-use-f: Navigation (compass icon), World (globe icon), Address (map-marker icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.map.use-for: Show on map; Open map; Show directions
i18n.icons.descriptions.menu.description: The menu icon represents a list shown on the display of a computer from which a user can select.
i18n.icons.descriptions.menu.do-not-use-: Navigation (compass icon), Show more options (more icon), Show apps overview (apps icon), List (list icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.microphone-slash: The slashed microphone icon represents an instrument for converting sound waves into electrical energy variations which may then be amplified, transmitted, or recorded.
Microphone enabled/supported (microphone icon), Phone (phone icon), Headset/Headphones (headphones icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.microphone.descr: The microphone icon represents an instrument for converting sound waves into electrical energy variations which may then be amplified, transmitted, or recorded.
i18n.icons.descriptions.microphone.do-no: Microphone muted/disabled (microphone-slash icon), Phone (phone icon), Headset/Headphones (headphones icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.minus.descriptio: The minus icon represents the mathematical minus sign, which indicates an operation of subtraction.
i18n.icons.descriptions.minus.do-not-use: Delete (trash icon), Erase (eraser icon), Cancel (cancel icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.mobile.descripti: The mobile icon represents a portable, cordless telephone for use in a cellular system.
i18n.icons.descriptions.mobile.do-not-us: Phone/Telephone number (phone icon), Tablet (tablet icon), Take picture (camera icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.more.description: The more icon represents a greater or additional amount or degree of something.
i18n.icons.descriptions.more.do-not-use-: Show menu (menu icon), Show apps overview (apps icon), Draggable (drag-indicator icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.paper-plane.desc: The paper plane icon represents a airplane made of paper, indicating sending something.
i18n.icons.descriptions.pen.description: The pen icon represents an implement for writing or drawing with ink or a similar fluid.
i18n.icons.descriptions.pen.do-not-use-f: Add (plus icon), Paint (brush icon), Author (user-pen icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.phone.descriptio: The phone icon represents an instrument used for transmitting voices over a distance using wire or radio, by converting acoustic vibrations to electrical signals.
i18n.icons.descriptions.pin.description: The pin icon represents a thin piece of metal with a sharp point at one end and a head at the other, used for fastening pieces of cloth or paper.
i18n.icons.descriptions.play.description: The play icon represents anything closely related to a video.
i18n.icons.descriptions.plus-circle.desc: The PlusCircle represents a plus icon enclosed in a circle.
i18n.icons.descriptions.plus.description: The plus icon represents the mathematical plus sign, which indicates an operation of addition.
i18n.icons.descriptions.plus.do-not-use-: Edit (pen icon), Confirm (checkmark icon), Save (save icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.printer.descript: The printer icon represents a machine for printing text or pictures, especially one linked to a computer.
i18n.icons.descriptions.qrcode.descripti: The QR code icon represents a machine-readable code consisting of an array of black and white squares, typically used for storing URLs or other information for reading by the camera on a smartphone.
i18n.icons.descriptions.random.descripti: The random icon represents making, doing, or choosing at random.
i18n.icons.descriptions.refresh.descript: The refresh icon represents updating or renewing something, such as an image or the displayed data on a web page.
i18n.icons.descriptions.repeat.descripti: The repeat icon represents saying, doing, or accomplishing something again
i18n.icons.descriptions.reply.descriptio: The reply icon represents the action of answering someone or something, i.e writing back in answer to someone.
i18n.icons.descriptions.rss.description: The reply icon represents RSS, a computer document format that enables updates to websites to be easily distributed.
i18n.icons.descriptions.rss.use-for: RSS feed available; Subscribe to rss feed
i18n.icons.descriptions.save.description: The save icon represents a thin plastic disk coated with magnetic material on which data for a computer can be stored respectively saved.
i18n.icons.descriptions.scroll.descripti: The scroll icon represents a roll (as of papyrus, leather, or parchment) for writing a document.
i18n.icons.descriptions.scroll.use-for: List; List of statements; List of official/formal things
i18n.icons.descriptions.search.descripti: The search icon represents a specially shaped piece of glass that is attached to a handle and is used to make an object look larger than it is.
i18n.icons.descriptions.server.descripti: The server icon represents a computer in a network that is used to provide services (such as access to files or shared peripherals or the routing of email) to other computers in the network.
i18n.icons.descriptions.server.do-not-us: PC (desktop icon), Database (database icon), Cloud (cloud icon), File created by system (file-server icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.share.descriptio: The share icon represents distributing or posting something on the Internet or on a social media platform.
i18n.icons.descriptions.shopping-cart.de: The shopping cart icon represents a metal or plastic cart with four small wheels that is used for holding merchandise when shopping.
i18n.icons.descriptions.shopping-cart.us: Show shopping cart; Add to shopping cart
i18n.icons.descriptions.sign-language.de: The sign language icon represents any of various formal languages employing a system of hand gestures and their placement relative to the upper body, facial expressions, body postures, and finger spelling especially for communication by and with deaf people.
i18n.icons.descriptions.smile.descriptio: The smile icon represents an expression of pleasure.
i18n.icons.descriptions.speech-bubble.de: The speech bubble icon represents the round or rectangular shape next to the head of a character in a cartoon inside which the character"s words or thoughts are written.
i18n.icons.descriptions.stack.descriptio: The stack icon represents a pile of objects, typically one that is neatly arranged.
i18n.icons.descriptions.star-filled.desc: The filled star icon represents a given star of a group of conventional stars used to place something in a scale of value.
i18n.icons.descriptions.star-filled.do-n: Binary rating (thumbs-up/thumbs-down icon), Like (heart icon), Flagging (flag icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.star.description: The star icon represents one of a group of conventional stars used to place something in a scale of value.
i18n.icons.descriptions.star.do-not-use-: Binary rating (thumbs-up/thumbs-down icon), Like (heart icon), Flagging (flag icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.stop.description: The stop icon represents keeping from carrying out a proposed action or causing an action, process, or event to come to an end.
i18n.icons.descriptions.stop.do-not-use-: Sign language (sign-language icon), Indicate prohibited/inactive action (ban icon), Cancel change (cancel icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.tablet.descripti: The tablet icon represents a small portable computer that accepts input directly on to its screen rather than via a keyboard or mouse.
i18n.icons.descriptions.tablet.do-not-us: Smartphone/Mobile (mobile icon), PC (desktop icon), Take picture (camera icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.tablet.use-for: Tablet; Open in app on tablet
i18n.icons.descriptions.tachometer.descr: The tachometer icon represents a device for indicating speed of rotation.
i18n.icons.descriptions.tachometer.use-f: Show metrics; Show system overview; Show management summary; Show dashboard
i18n.icons.descriptions.tag.description: The tag icon represents a cardboard, plastic, or metal marker used for identification, description or classification.
i18n.icons.descriptions.tag.do-not-use-f: Flagging/Tagging (flag icon), Payment (credit-card icon), Ticket (ticket icon), Price (coins icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.thumbs-down.desc: The thumbs down icon represents an instance or gesture of rejection, disapproval, or condemnation.
i18n.icons.descriptions.thumbs-down.do-n: Non-binary rating (star icon), Unhappiness/Not good (frown icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.thumbs-up.descri: The thumbs up icon represents an instance or gesture of approval or encouragement.
i18n.icons.descriptions.thumbs-up.do-not: Non-binary rating (star icon), Happiness/Good (smile icon), Like (heart icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.ticket.descripti: The ticket icon represents a piece of paper or card that gives the holder a certain right, especially to enter a place, travel by public transport, or participate in an event.
i18n.icons.descriptions.trash.descriptio: The trash icon represents a container for things that are no longer useful or wanted and that have been thrown away.
i18n.icons.descriptions.trash.do-not-use: Cancel (cancel icon), Erase (eraser icon), Stop (stop icon), Remove row (minus icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.truck.descriptio: The truck icon represents a wheeled vehicle for moving heavy freight or goods.
i18n.icons.descriptions.undo.description: The undo icon represents a circling arrow pointing to the left
i18n.icons.descriptions.universal-access: The universal access icon represents equal access for all people to participate in a system, i.e people with impairments.
i18n.icons.descriptions.university.descr: The university icon represents an institution of higher learning providing facilities for teaching and research and authorized to grant academic degrees.
i18n.icons.descriptions.unlink.descripti: The unlink icon represents two separated links of a broken chain.
i18n.icons.descriptions.unlink.do-not-us: Link to external page or resource (external icon), Link (link icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.unlock.descripti: The unlock icon represents a open removable lock with a shackle that can be passed through a staple or link and then secured.
i18n.icons.descriptions.unlock.do-not-us: Access (key icon), Lock/Locked (lock icon), Fix/Lock in position (pin icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.upload.descripti: The upload icon represents transferring data or files from a pc, smartphone or other storage device to a system.
i18n.icons.descriptions.upload.do-not-us: Download (download icon), Logout (logout icon), Upload to cloud (cloud-upload icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.user-brush.descr: The user brush icon represents a person who is a designer or artist.
i18n.icons.descriptions.user-brush.do-no: Developer (user-code icon), Unspecified user (user icon), Author (user-pen icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.user-checkmark.d: The user checkmark icon represents a person who has been verified.
i18n.icons.descriptions.user-code.descri: The user code icon represents a person who is a developer.
i18n.icons.descriptions.user-code.do-not: Designer/Artist (user-brush icon), Unspecified user (user icon), Author (user-pen icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.user-cog.descrip: The user cog icon represents user specific settings.
i18n.icons.descriptions.user-pen.descrip: The user pen icon represents a person, who is the author of a record.
i18n.icons.descriptions.user.description: The user icon represents a person who uses or operates something.
i18n.icons.descriptions.user.do-not-use-: User settings (user-cog icon), Developer (user-code icon), Designer (user-brush icon), Author (user-pen icon), Users (users icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.users.descriptio: The users icon represents a group of users.
i18n.icons.descriptions.video.descriptio: The video icon represents a recording of visual images and sound, as of a television production, made on magnetic tape.
i18n.icons.descriptions.wand.description: The wand icon represents a rod thought to have magic properties, used in casting spells or performing conjuring tricks.
i18n.icons.descriptions.wand.do-not-use-: Probe (eyedropper icon), Edit (pen icon), Paint (brush icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.wand.use-for: “Magic“ or automatic selection; Perform automated action
i18n.icons.descriptions.warning-circle.d: The warning circle icon represents a distinctive indication of major significance, interest, or contrast.
i18n.icons.descriptions.warning-circle.u: Highlight input field with wrong data
i18n.icons.descriptions.warning-triangle: The warning triangle icon represents a triangle placed by a broken-down car to warn motorists to avoid it.
Warning if warning icon is not appropriate/strong enough
i18n.icons.descriptions.warning.descript: The warning icon represents a distinctive indication of major significance, interest, or contrast.
i18n.icons.descriptions.warning.do-not-u: Highlight input field with wrong data (warning-circle icon)
i18n.icons.descriptions.weight.descripti: The weight icon represents a weight, often used for measuring weight with a balance.
i18n.icons.descriptions.wheelchair.descr: The wheelchair icon represents a chair mounted on wheels especially for the use of disabled persons.
i18n.icons.descriptions.wi-fi.descriptio: The Wi-Fi icon represents a facility allowing computers, smartphones, or other devices to connect to the internet or communicate with one another wireless within a particular area.
i18n.icons.descriptions.wrench.descripti: The wrench icon represents a hand or power tool for holding, twisting, or turning an object, such as a bolt or nut.
i18n.notification.sampleMessage: This is a sample message {{message}} and {{parameters}}
